pos_mean_info_list.mean: 本地人；土著；动植物的自生种；本地产的动植物（等于indigene）

bilingual.source: Here it is, some indigenous life down here.
bilingual.target: 看，有些土生土长的生物。

bilingual.source: Indigenous peoples and conquerors gradually coalesced into the present-day population.
bilingual.target: 土生土长的人们和征服者们逐渐合并成现在的居民人口。

bilingual.source: Indigenous. The indigenous tribe has never had contact with outside humans.
bilingual.target: 土生土长的。土生土长的部落从未和外界人类有过接触。

bilingual.source: The overwhelming majority of the indigenous English are, in fact, BCs.
bilingual.target: 事实上，绝大多数土生土长的英国人属于BC级。

bilingual.source: Indigenous descirbes a plant, animal or person that is native to an area.
bilingual.target: “Indigenous”描述的是在一个地区土生土长的植物，动物或人。

bilingual.source: Indigenous peoples and conquerors gradually coalesced into the present - day population.
bilingual.target: 土生土长的人们和征服者们逐渐合并成现在的居民人口.

bilingual.source: An indigenous South American rodent, the chinchilla offers another example of how dangerous it can be to be cuddly.
bilingual.target: 龙猫是土生土长的南美洲啮齿动物。别看它长相萌人，其实也不是个好惹的家伙。

bilingual.source: But indigenous Oaxacan mothers traditionally breast feed their babies for a year and rarely use bassinets, carrying their infants instead in a rebozo, a type of sling.
bilingual.target: 但是土生土长的瓦哈卡母亲向来是亲自哺乳喂养，习惯抱着孩子，很少用摇篮，也不用吊兜。

bilingual.source: She introduced me to indigenous philosophy and showed me that there was an incredibly deep a valid intrepretation of the world that had been born and nurtured in North America.
bilingual.target: 她引导我认识了土著人的哲学思想，并告诉我：有一种合理的方式可以解释这些在北美洲土生土长的人的生存方式。 这种方式非常深刻，让人难以置信。

bilingual.source: It is extremely beautiful and you can experience the indigenous Australia there more than anywhere else.
bilingual.target: 那里非常美丽，你可以比在其他地方更多地体验到澳大利亚的原住民文化。

list.abstract: indigenous [inˈdidʒinəs] adj. 土生土长的 Kangaroos are indigenous to Australia. 袋鼠为澳大利亚本地的动物。 生来的, 固有的 Each country has its own indigenous cultural tradition. 每个国家都有其自身的文化传统。

yingyinNormal.en: We have an indigenous population of humanoids called the Na'vi.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里有种人形土著称为纳威族。

yingyinNormal.en: Let me try again. Have the indigenous fauna accepted you as one of their own? Nudge, nudge, wink, wink. Oh, I guess so.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我再试一次好了。这几个“本地物种”接受你为他们中一员了吗？咯吱咯吱，使使眼色。我想是吧。

yingyinNormal.en: We build them a school, we teach them English, but after, what, how many years? Relations with the indigenous are only getting worse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们为他们建造学校，教他们英语但之后呢？多少年过去了，我们和当地土著的关系只是更恶化了。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.zh: 本地的; 土生土长的

examination_example.sentence: Well, it follows my expedition to study the vegetation <highlight>indigenous</highlight> to the rain forest in equatorial areas of southeast Asia.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 嗯，它跟随着我一起研究东南亚赤道地区热带雨林的原生植被。

examination_example.sentence: Currently, under an aggressive Hindu nationalist government, Muslims, Christians, disadvantaged classes and <highlight>indigenous</highlight> communities are being compelled to give up their traditional foods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 目前，在激进的印度教民族主义政府的统治下，穆斯林基督徒、弱势阶层和土著社区正被迫放弃他们的传统食物。

examination_example.sentence: Some of its <highlight>indigenous</highlight> languages are dying out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它的一些土著语言正在消亡。
